BRIEFLY; HEALTH: UCLA CENTER TO BE NAMED FOR ARTHUR ASHE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The new student health and wellness center under construction at UCLA will be 
named in honor of the late tennis star Arthur Ashe. 
</P>
<P>
 The Arthur Ashe Student Health and Wellness Center will replace the current 
facility housed at the Center for Health Sciences. The 36,000-square-foot 
building in the center of campus is scheduled to be completed in two years. 
</P>
<P>
 Ashe, who was captain of the UCLA tennis team in 1965, died of AIDS in 
February, 1993. 
</P>
