<HEADLINE>
<P>
TRIED & TRUE; PARK HAS NON-SCARE FARE FOR KIDS AT CAMP SPOOKY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CORINNE FLOCKEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Even though Knott's "Halloween Haunt" boasts hangings and horrifying mutants, 
that doesn't mean you can't bring the kiddies.  
</P>
<P>
 For the little thrill-seekers among us, Knott's offers Camp Spooky.On Oct. 22, 
23, 29 and 30, the park offers non-scare fare for children 3 to 11. Held in the 
Camp Snoopy children's area from 10 a.m. to 6 p.m. (the scary folks take over 
the park at 7 p.m.), Camp Spooky features trick-or-treat stations, contests, a 
kid-sized maze, pumpkin-carving demonstrations and Halloween-themed workshops.  
</P>
<P>
 There will be costume contests, and children are encouraged to come tricked 
out in their Halloween best. 
</P>
<P>
 Camp Spooky is free with park admission of $28.50 for adults and $18.50 for 
children ages 3 to 11 and senior citizens. For details, call (714) 220-5200. 
CORINNE FLOCKEN 
</P>
</TEXT>
