<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: MISCELLANY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 In an effort to prevent a repeat of last year's Rose Bowl scam that left 
hundreds of Wisconsin fans without tickets to the game, the federal government 
proposed rules to monitor air ticket operators.Under the Truth in Ticketing 
rules, expected to go into effect by December, operators who offer package 
deals to events without having tickets would be banned by the Department of 
Transportation. 
</P>
<P>
 The NCAA Council endorsed a proposal by the President's Commission to relax 
restrictions on partial qualifiers -- incoming freshman who do not meet all of 
the academic requirements. 
</P>
<P>
 Back spasms sent Paul Azinger to the sidelines and placed in jeopardy his 
chances of playing this week in the Texas Open. 
</P>
</TEXT>
