<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: GARDENA; COUNCIL SUPPORTS PLAN FOR SHOPPING COMPLEX 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By SUSAN WOODWARD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The City Council has tentatively approved controversial plans to construct a 
54,000-square-foot shopping complex at Artesia Boulevard and Vermont Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
 Council members unanimously supported the plan for a Smith's Food and Drug 
Center after a public hearing on the issue Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
 The three-hour hearing drew many public comments for and against the 
development. 
</P>
<P>
 Opponents want the city to use the eight acres of vacant land for a park, 
incorporating a wetland, known as the Gardena Willows, which is next to the 
site. 
</P>
<P>
 The council is expected to officially approve the center at its Oct. 25 
meeting. SUSAN WOODWARD 
