<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: RANCHO PALOS VERDES; RESTRICTED ACCESS OKD FOR ISLAND VIEW 
TRACT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF KASS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Residents of the Island View housing tract have gained preliminary approval to 
restrict access to the public streets surrounding their homes. 
</P>
<P>
 Last week, the City Council voted 4 to 1 to begin proceedings to hand over a 
small part of Whitley Collins Street near Crest Road to the Island View Home 
Owners' Assn. 
</P>
<P>
 The association plans to build a card-controlled gate that would restrict 
access to approved cars. Pedestrian access to the estimated 90 homes would not 
be restricted. 
</P>
<P>
 In an effort to curb crime, the association has asked to restrict access three 
times since 1992, according to a city report. 
</P>
<P>
 Because restricting access to public roadways may open the city to a lawsuit, 
the homeowners' association must also pay the city's legal fees if the 
arrangement wins final approval. 
</P>
<P>
 Mayor Steven Kuykendall, who voted against the measure, said he was worried 
about a lawsuit against the city. State law prohibits a city from restricting 
access to public streets. 
</P>
<P>
 But City Atty. Carol Lynch said such an action may be legal if part of the 
street is private. JEFF KASS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
