EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; TICKETS STILL AVAILABLE FOR PLAZA 
OPENING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A limited number of tickets are still available for the grand opening of the 
Thousand Oaks Civic Arts Plaza on Oct. 21 and 22, theater officials say. 
</P>
<P>
 The grand opening includes a performance by Tony-award winning entertainer 
Bernadette Peters and the Conejo Symphony Orchestra.A black-tie reception will 
follow the Oct. 22 show. 
</P>
<P>
 Only balcony seats are available in the 1,800-seat theater, at prices ranging 
from $50 to $75. 
</P>
<P>
 Peters is a singer and an actress who switches regularly from Broadway 
musicals to television specials and quirky, comedic appearances in movies. 
</P>
<P>
 The Conejo Symphony Orchestra will play Beethoven's "Ode to Joy," accompanied 
by a 200-voice choir. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in tickets or information can contact the Civic Arts Plaza 
box office at 449-ARTS. MARY F. POLS 
