</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAIA DAVIS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Both serious runners and the not-so-serious will hit the road in downtown 
Ventura later this month for a race to benefit local school libraries. 
</P>
<P>
 Called the Roads Scholars Race, the event will be held Oct. 23, with the first 
race to start at 8 a.m. 
</P>
<P>
 In addition to competitive runners, the race is expected to draw many 
students, including a group of middle-school children who plan to dress as a 
centipede. 
</P>
<P>
 Last year's race drew more than 1,000 runners, netting $12,000 for the Ventura 
Unified School District. Organizers hope to raise more this year and to funnel 
all proceeds into libraries at the district's 24 schools. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will include a 10K, 5K and one-mile race. Entry fees range from $10 
to $16 until Friday. After Friday, each fee will increase by $4. 
</P>
<P>
 For information or to sign up for a race, call Fleet Feet Sports at 644-9712. 
