<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; BROTHERS GIVEN LIFE TERMS IN '93 SLAYING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two brothers convicted of raping a woman with a baseball bat, kicking her with 
steel-toed boots and fatally shooting her, execution-style, were sentenced 
Wednesday to life in prison without the possibility of parole. 
</P>
<P>
 Van Nuys Superior Court Judge Kathryne Ann Stoltz sentenced Alejandro Verdugo, 
24, and his brother, Daniel, 22, following a brief hearing. 
</P>
<P>
 Because prosecutors did not seek the death penalty, the sentence was the 
maximum the law allowed. 
</P>
<P>
 The February, 1993, incident provided a brutal end to the victim's difficult 
life. According to a probation report, Suzanne Shapiro, 34, was given to a 
religious cult as a child. At one point, she had been married to the late Max 
Shapiro, one of Elvis Presley's doctors. 
</P>
<P>
 She had been drinking the night she died at the Dugout Lounge, a Van Nuys bar. 
She was accosted in the parking lot, where her body was found the next morning. 
ANN W. O'NEILL 
</P>
</TEXT>
