<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANNUAL BIKE TOUR TO PROMOTE CITY TRAILS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's Bicycle Trails Advisory Committee will host its 10th annual Bicycle 
Tour of Newport on Sunday to promote awareness of the city's bicycle trail 
network. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event will begin at 10a.m. at the Newport Dunes aquatic resort, 1131 
Backbay Drive, and will cover nine miles of the Upper Newport Bay bikeway. 
Helmets are strongly suggested for all riders and are mandatory for those under 
17. 
</P>
<P>
 The event will also include bicycle maintenance presentations, information 
about the back bay and free T-shirts for participants. 
</P>
<P>
 Registration is free, but a form must be completed before the event. For more 
information or to request a form, call (714) 644-3311. 
</P>
