<HEADLINE>
<P>
ANNUAL STORYTELLING FESTIVAL THIS WEEKEND 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The city's fourth annual Storytelling Festival will take place Friday and 
Saturday at the San Juan Capistrano Library Courtyard and Auditorium. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival, sponsored by the city, will include readings for people of all 
ages, plus workshops designed for teachers. 
</P>
<P>
 The festival will feature some of the nation's best storytellers, including 
Diane Ferlatte of Oakland and Martha Holloway of La Jolla. 
</P>
<P>
 Newcomers to this year's festival will include storytellers Donald Davis of 
Ocracoke Island, N.C., Olga Loya of San Jose and Johnny Moses of La Conner, 
Wash. 
</P>
<P>
 For tickets and schedule information, call (714) 768-1916. 
