 When reader Mary Weaver of Manhattan Beach became president of a local women's 
group, her family made a big deal out of it. But her grandson, 3, had only one 
question: 
</P>
<P>
 "Grandma, now that you are president, when do you get your picture on the 
money?"  
</P>
