<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEW CARS AND A MOVIE 'STAR' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LAURIE K. SCHENDEN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Car commercials have been known to show some pretty brutal tests for endurance 
and handling, but none compare to the video you'll see next to a certain Ford 
Explorer at the Long Beach Auto Show. 
</P>
<P>
 The video shows clips from the film "Jurassic Park," and the Explorers in the 
film are chomped on, flung around and pretty much demolished by unruly 
Tyrannosauruses. 
</P>
<P>
 The "Jurassic Park" display is just one of the attractions at the auto show at 
Long Beach Convention Center, 300 E. Ocean Blvd. 
</P>
<P>
 Other highlights include the Team Rollerblade stunt exhibition (Saturday) and, 
of course, new car models, including the Chrysler Cirrus, Toyota Avalon, 
Pontiac Sunfire and a Sunfire Speedster concept car. 
</P>
<P>
 You'll also have a chance to dribble and shoot baskets with the Laker Girls -- 
and win Lakers tickets in the bargain. 
</P>
<P>
 The show opened Wednesday and runs daily through Sunday, 10 a.m.-10 p.m.; 
Sunday, 10 a.m.-7 p.m. $6 (look for discounts at Thrifty and Chief Auto Parts); 
seniors, $4; children 6-12, $3; under 6, free. (310) 499-7692. LAURIE K. 
SCHENDEN 
</P>
