TRUSTEE CANDIDATES TO HAVE 2 FORUMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Orange County's League of Women Voters will moderate two candidate forums this 
month for Newport-Mesa Unified School District board candidates. 
</P>
<P>
 Three incumbents are leaving the seven-member board and one is seeking 
reelection.The unexpected departure of veteran board member Roderick H. 
MacMillian opens a seat that many previously thought was unattainable. 
</P>
<P>
 When MacMillian dropped out last week, citing ill health, only one opponent 
had filed for candidacy in Trustee Area 7. Since then, another has filed as a 
write-in candidate and others have indicated they are considering entering the 
race. 
</P>
<P>
 League spokeswoman Judy Gielow said only candidates who have filed with the 
registrar of voters' office will be invited to the candidate forums. 
</P>
<P>
 They are scheduled Wednesday in the Loats Performing Arts Center at Newport 
Harbor High School, and Oct. 27 at the Little Theater at Corona del Mar High 
School. Both will begin at 7 p.m. and end by 9, Gielow said. 
</P>
<P>
 The forums, co-sponsored by the schools' PTAs and committees, are open to all 
Newport-Mesa voters. Candidates will draw lots for the order in which they will 
respond to questions solicited from the audience and screened for language and 
duplication by League members. 
</P>
<P>
 Gielow said civics teachers at both high schools have been asked to have 
students prepare questions and select representatives to ask them at the 
forums. 
</P>
