<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: COMPTON; SCHOOL BOARD SEEKING DYMALLY REPLACEMENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN D. WAGNER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 School officials are accepting applications to fill the seat formerly held by 
Lynn Dymally, who was ousted last month after she had not attended a school 
board meeting in a year. 
</P>
<P>
 A committee of community members will screen the applicants.The filing 
deadline is Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
 Board officials are expected to announce a successor to Dymally at their Nov. 
8 meeting. Although the board is only an advisory body to state-appointed 
administrator Jerome Harris, it has the authority to fill a vacant seat, 
district and county education officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 The new board member will serve the remainder of Dymally's term, which is 
scheduled to expire in November, 1995.  
</P>
<P>
 Dymally was removed after several unexcused absences. She has refused to 
comment on her absences.  
</P>
<P>
 Applications for the unpaid position are available at the superintendent's 
office, 604 S. Tamarind Ave. Those applying must be at least 18, a U.S. citizen 
and a resident in the school district. JOHN D. WAGNER 
</P>
</TEXT>
