<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: PASADENA; 3 CHURCH GROUPS URGE DEFEAT OF PROP. 187 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Three coalitions of Pasadena-area churches are calling for the defeat of 
Proposition 187, which would deny most public services to illegal immigrants if 
approved Nov. 8. 
</P>
<P>
 The Ecumenical Council of Pasadena Area Churches, which represents 38 
congregations of different denominations; the Interdenominational Ministerial 
Alliance of Greater Pasadena, comprising 32 mostly African American 
congregations, and Altadena Congregations Together Serving, representing nine 
interfaith religious bodies, said they oppose the measure. 
</P>
<P>
 Leaders of the groups said "the most vulnerable children will be victims of 
Proposition 187," which would bar the children of illegal immigrants from 
attending public school. 
</P>
<P>
 The groups called Proposition 187 "one of the clearest moral issues to 
confront California voters in many years." 
</P>
