FAMOUS ALUMNI GIVE STANFORD $77.4 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Stanford University alumni William R. Hewlett and David Packard have given 
their alma mater its largest single donation ever: $77.4 million. 
</P>
<P>
 The gift will be used to construct four buildings for science and engineering 
studies, renovate others and create a landscaped mall, Stanford President 
Gerhard Casper said. 
</P>
<P>
 "We believe this gift will ensure that Stanford University will have 
leadership in science and engineering second to none during the 21st Century," 
Hewlett and Packard said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
 The two are co-founders of Hewlett-Packard, one of the nation's largest 
computer companies. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction of the new complex is to begin in the fall and will be completed 
by the fall of 1999. 
